snippet.textDisplay:
the reason the orange popped the balloon is because of how citric and ascorbic the acid (and limonene juice) in the juice is. just like the acid in our stomach that can literally DISSOLVE metal, it’s called hydrochloric acid. different acids can dissolve things, just like if you squeeze some lemon juice into a bowl with liquid soap detergent for dishes and baking soda will scrub off PERMANENT or any black hair dye of off skin and hard surfaces such as wood. so yeah acid is very strong, that’s why most of us have acid reflux if we eat too many oranges or citric fruits !

basically (for a shorter answer) -> the rubber (balloon) melts in the limonene juice!
